value.value: An eyelid connective tissue that is part of a hypodermis.
A basement membrane that is part of a nephron tubule.
A basement membrane that is part of a bronchus.
A basement membrane that is part of a trachea.
A branch of the maxillary artery that is found in the gingiva, premolars, and molars.
An artery that supplies oxygenated blood to the ear.
Nucleus located in the midbrain.
Nucleus located within the hindbrain.
A nucleus of brain that is part of a telencephalon.
Ventral mesentery is the part of the peritoneum closest to the navel.
An anatomical space that surrounded_by a embryonic cloaca.
An anatomical space that surrounded_by a rectum.

The nasal fin is an epithelial seam that develops by fusion between the epithelial linings of the medial and lateral nasal swellings. Shortly after its formation the nasal fin regresses and is replaced by mesenchyme, with exception of its most posterior portion which remains as the bucconasal membrane.
The oronasal membrane separates the oral cavity and nasal cavity.
Anatomical cluster consisting of adjacent teeth constituting a row.
A tooth row that is part of a skeleton of lower jaw.
A tooth row that is part of a skeleton of upper jaw.
A basilar artery branch that supplies the anterior portion of the inferior surface of the cerebellum.
An organ cavity that is part of a pharyngotympanic tube.
An epithelium that is part of a hypopharynx.
Any endocardium that is part of the right ventricle of the heart.
Any endocardium that is part of the left ventricle of the heart.

The primordial mass of tissue formed by the merging of the medial nasal prominences of the embryo; it contributes to the intermaxillary portion of the upper jaw, the prolabial portion of the upper lip, and the primary palate.
An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a stomodeum.
The cavity of the developing embryo that is formed within the epiblast tissue prior to the closing of the proamniotic canal by the amniotic folds.
The closed space containing the yolk, formed by the fusion of the edges of the embryonic epiblast (hypoblast) and later surrounded by the visceral yolk sac (hypoblast and visceral yolk sac mesoderm).

The channels in the lymph node medulla that separate the medullary cords and are crossed by a reticulum of cells and fibers and bounded by littoral cells; lymph flows through the medullary sinus from the cortical sinuses and into the efferent lymphatic vessels.

definition.value: Lymph flows into the medullary sinuses from cortical sinuses, and into efferent lymphatic vessels. Medullary sinuses contain histiocytes (immobile macrophages) and reticular cells.[WP]

value.value: The dense rope-like structures of lymphatic tissue located between the medullary sinuses in the medulla of a lymph node.
The crescent-shaped, ventrally located fold of the embryonic disc at the future cephalic end of the developing embryo.
The crescent-shaped, ventrally located fold of the embryonic disc at the future caudal end of the developing embryo.
The elevated margins of the neural groove that are located in the future cephalic region of the embryo.

The primordial embryonic connective tissue of the developing limbs, autopods and digits, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to limb connective tissue, bone and musculature in conjunction with myotome cells.
The embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing cardiac structures.
The embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing pancreas.
A ganglion that is part of a abdominal segment of trunk.
An inter-phalangeal joint that connects a proximal phalanx to either a medial or distal phalanx.
An inter-phalangeal joint that connects a distal phalanx to either a medial or proximal phalanx.
An anterior cardinal vein that is in_the_left_side_of a multicellular organism.
An anterior cardinal vein that is in_the_right_side_of a multicellular organism.
A renal tubule is a tube that filters, re-absorbs and secretes substances to rid an organism of waste and to play a role in fluid homeostasis.
A serous sac that has the pleura and the pleural cavity as parts.

value.value: A cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a right atrium auricular region.

label.value: cardiac muscle tissue of left auricle

value.value: A cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a left atrium auricular region.
